                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10271: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 29, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>238. Your 421, September 27, 5 p.m., first sentence. Telegram received this
                    morning from authoritative source states that on September 28 eleven Japanese
                    bombers raided Nanking and dropped bombs in the vicinity of the Commercial Air
                    Field.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
